hopobject.body: History lec medical pe 207 Obviously, many of these properties need improvement to make them habitable. Their new owners would incur the cost of upgrades. And, in a virtuous circle, the resulting surge in construction would create thousands of new jobs that the city desperately needs. No doubt some hard-hearted conservatives will decry the housing "giveaway," but the alternative is to let vacant properties keep decaying.
